1
00:00:04,771 --> 00:00:07,206
I don't want to do the dance.

2
00:00:07,207 --> 00:00:08,507
<i>Then ask to be removed.</i>

3
00:00:08,508 --> 00:00:10,275
<i>But that just doesn't fit my image.</i>

4
00:00:10,276 --> 00:00:11,510
<i>But apparently, Nobunaga</i>

5
00:00:11,511 --> 00:00:13,512
<i>actually ran away from a battle once.</i>

6
00:00:13,513 --> 00:00:15,514
But I don't think it's lame.

7
00:00:15,515 --> 00:00:17,349
<i>It's kind of cool how</i>

8
00:00:17,350 --> 00:00:19,085
<i>he bares all his weaknesses, huh?</i>

9
00:00:19,686 --> 00:00:20,753
<i>Saku,</i>

10
00:00:20,754 --> 00:00:21,954
‎PREVIOUSLY ON <i>‎TATSUKI: TOO KIND FOR SCHOOL</i>

11
00:00:21,955 --> 00:00:23,322
<i>you can become Nobunaga too.</i>

12
00:00:23,323 --> 00:00:27,060
Saku! Go! You can do it!

13
00:00:30,463 --> 00:00:31,697
Yeah!

14
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:34,000
Tatsuki! Sora jumped.

15
00:00:42,942 --> 00:00:44,443
YUKANAI

16
00:00:44,444 --> 00:00:46,879
IT'S ALMOST SUMMER VACATION!
WE WILL BE OPEN DURING SUMMER VACATION

17
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:49,581
I will give you this award to honor
your achievements

18
00:00:49,582 --> 00:00:51,483
this past month.

19
00:00:51,484 --> 00:00:52,485
- Here are some beads.
- Check.

20
00:00:54,521 --> 00:00:55,989
Oh, you got me.

21
00:00:56,556 --> 00:00:57,390
Hey.

22
00:00:57,891 --> 00:01:00,026
I've been wondering for a while,
but who's that man?

23
00:01:01,227 --> 00:01:02,461
Oh, that's Mr. Eiraku.

24
00:01:02,462 --> 00:01:03,629
He comes every now and then

25
00:01:03,630 --> 00:01:06,198
to teach us all sorts of old-school games.

26
00:01:06,199 --> 00:01:07,566
He's not a strong player though,

27
00:01:07,567 --> 00:01:08,735
so he’s pretty popular.

28
00:01:09,335 --> 00:01:10,637
I see.

29
00:01:12,472 --> 00:01:14,606
All right, it's time to clean up!

30
00:01:14,607 --> 00:01:17,342
We're in the middle of a good game,
so give us some time.

31
00:01:17,343 --> 00:01:18,610
But it's cleaning day.

32
00:01:18,611 --> 00:01:21,181
Meanie.

33
00:01:22,582 --> 00:01:23,950
Oh no, the paint dripped.

34
00:01:24,451 --> 00:01:26,018
Oh no.

35
00:01:26,019 --> 00:01:28,555
It was turning out so well too.

36
00:01:29,522 --> 00:01:30,956
What a shocking failure.

37
00:01:30,957 --> 00:01:33,693
- Shock-man.
- It's okay. Let me see it.

38
00:01:34,260 --> 00:01:36,196
I'll show you how to fix it.

39
00:01:39,766 --> 00:01:42,235
And then…

40
00:01:42,735 --> 00:01:45,071
Go like this.

41
00:01:47,674 --> 00:01:50,175
- Wow.
- It's so pretty.

42
00:01:50,176 --> 00:01:52,444
Everyone, it's almost time to clean up.

43
00:01:52,445 --> 00:01:53,879
Whoa, the demon is here.

44
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:55,247
What?

45
00:01:55,248 --> 00:01:56,748
Who are you calling a demon?

46
00:01:56,749 --> 00:01:58,650
- So scary!
- Oh no!

47
00:01:58,651 --> 00:01:59,751
Come on.

48
00:01:59,752 --> 00:02:01,186
- Start cleaning up.
- Seiryu.

49
00:02:01,187 --> 00:02:02,721
Here. How about this?

50
00:02:02,722 --> 00:02:04,690
Wow.

51
00:02:04,691 --> 00:02:06,058
- It's amazing.
- Right?

52
00:02:06,059 --> 00:02:07,025
Let's add more color--

53
00:02:07,026 --> 00:02:08,428
Hurry up and clean!

54
00:02:09,095 --> 00:02:10,929
Run, everyone! Run!

55
00:02:10,930 --> 00:02:12,598
Don't let her catch you!

56
00:02:12,599 --> 00:02:14,500
It says that
there's going to be a barbecue.

57
00:02:14,501 --> 00:02:16,502
This is the schedule
for the summer vacation.

58
00:02:16,503 --> 00:02:18,604
Make sure you hand it to your mom and dad.

59
00:02:18,605 --> 00:02:20,706
- I'm so excited for this.
- Me too!

60
00:02:20,707 --> 00:02:21,874
Bye.

61
00:02:21,875 --> 00:02:23,275
- Bye.
- Bye.

62
00:02:23,276 --> 00:02:24,543
Be careful.

63
00:02:24,544 --> 00:02:26,879
- Hello.
- Bye.

64
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:28,681
Sorry I'm late.

65
00:02:29,249 --> 00:02:31,451
- Ms. Tachibana, you're here for a meeting?
- Yes.

66
00:02:33,119 --> 00:02:34,153
Sorry to make you wait.

67
00:02:34,154 --> 00:02:35,454
- Hello.
- Hello.

68
00:02:35,455 --> 00:02:36,455
Mr. Tatsuki.

69
00:02:36,456 --> 00:02:38,457
- What?
- You've got paint on your face.

70
00:02:38,458 --> 00:02:39,893
You've got paint on you.

71
00:02:43,363 --> 00:02:45,231
- It's still there.
- Forget it.

72
00:02:45,932 --> 00:02:48,600
How is Nene doing?

73
00:02:48,601 --> 00:02:49,636
Well,

74
00:02:50,637 --> 00:02:52,605
I'd like to cancel
her enrollment after this month.

75
00:02:54,707 --> 00:02:55,607
Is that right?

76
00:02:55,608 --> 00:02:56,543
Yes.

77
00:02:57,243 --> 00:03:00,747
Lately, my daughter isn't keen
on coming here anymore.

78
00:03:02,415 --> 00:03:06,319
Whether she wants to come or not
is entirely up to her, so that's okay,

79
00:03:07,086 --> 00:03:08,420
but is she unwell or something?

80
00:03:08,421 --> 00:03:10,990
No, not really.

81
00:03:12,525 --> 00:03:15,228
<i>She pretty much
stays holed up in her room,</i>

82
00:03:15,728 --> 00:03:18,631
<i>but she somehow manages to make it
to cram school and piano lessons.</i>

83
00:03:19,432 --> 00:03:20,266
I see.

84
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:23,502
So when she's not at those places,
she stays in her room?

85
00:03:23,503 --> 00:03:24,604
Yes.

86
00:03:25,939 --> 00:03:29,809
I just don't want her to end up
as a shut-in.

87
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:32,612
That's worrisome, isn't it?

88
00:03:33,379 --> 00:03:34,214
Yes.

89
00:03:34,781 --> 00:03:37,784
But you know, maybe she's enjoying
being a shut-in.

90
00:03:38,718 --> 00:03:40,719
- What?
- Enjoying it?

91
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:41,721
Yes.

92
00:03:43,356 --> 00:03:45,824
We actually have lots of events

93
00:03:45,825 --> 00:03:47,793
coming up this month,

94
00:03:47,794 --> 00:03:49,162
so please let Nene know.

95
00:03:50,730 --> 00:03:52,965
- Okay, will do.
- Thank you.

96
00:03:52,966 --> 00:03:54,534
- Thank you for your time.
- Thank you.

97
00:03:55,034 --> 00:03:56,502
I can see myself out.

98
00:03:57,003 --> 00:03:58,637
- Thank you.
- Take care.

99
00:03:58,638 --> 00:03:59,839
See you again.

100
00:04:03,676 --> 00:04:06,846
How does one enjoy being a shut-in?

101
00:04:10,183 --> 00:04:11,184
What?

102
00:04:12,018 --> 00:04:12,852
You don't know?

103
00:04:21,461 --> 00:04:23,296
I'm heading out now.

104
00:04:23,997 --> 00:04:26,465
Don't forget about
your piano lesson today.

105
00:04:26,466 --> 00:04:28,935
NENE

106
00:04:43,383 --> 00:04:45,451
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

107
00:04:47,820 --> 00:04:50,890
Mr. Sora Fujinaga
was discharged this morning.

108
00:04:51,457 --> 00:04:52,292
What?

109
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:56,296
- Is that right?
- Yes.

110
00:05:06,506 --> 00:05:08,840
YUKANAI SUMMER VACATION EVENT

111
00:05:08,841 --> 00:05:12,011
DIAMOND ART
LOTS OF DIFFERENT DESIGNS TO CHOOSE FROM!

112
00:05:15,648 --> 00:05:17,749
- What's this?
- Where are you, Shi-chan?

113
00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:19,451
- Wait, I'm scared.
- Where are you?

114
00:05:19,452 --> 00:05:21,153
- I found you!
- Wait!

115
00:05:21,154 --> 00:05:22,721
- There she is!
- Hold on!

116
00:05:22,722 --> 00:05:25,824
- Hold on!
- Shi-chan, you're so bad at this.

117
00:05:25,825 --> 00:05:27,492
I wasn't able to do anything yet.

118
00:05:27,493 --> 00:05:29,227
- You have to attack.
- Who's playing next?

119
00:05:29,228 --> 00:05:31,663
I thought I was attacking.

120
00:05:31,664 --> 00:05:32,665
Tatsuki is super strong.

121
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:34,434
Tatsuki is crazy good.

122
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:36,235
Really?

123
00:05:40,273 --> 00:05:41,774
Hi, Nene.

124
00:05:44,644 --> 00:05:46,879
Hello Nene.

125
00:05:47,714 --> 00:05:48,848
Hello.

126
00:05:52,885 --> 00:05:54,820
- You're so hyper.
- Kurumi, you're so fast.

127
00:05:54,821 --> 00:05:55,721
I am, huh?

128
00:05:55,722 --> 00:05:57,190
I'm always fast.

129
00:05:58,624 --> 00:05:59,726
Hey Nene.

130
00:06:01,527 --> 00:06:02,961
We just started.

131
00:06:02,962 --> 00:06:04,030
Come join us.

132
00:06:05,164 --> 00:06:06,265
Sit here.

133
00:06:06,866 --> 00:06:08,201
Okay.

134
00:06:08,835 --> 00:06:09,735
You can start

135
00:06:09,736 --> 00:06:12,171
by placing the gems
on the mane and the tail.

136
00:06:12,739 --> 00:06:16,109
- You can't be sloppy with this.
- I'm intent on finishing this.

137
00:06:17,510 --> 00:06:19,745
- You're so detailed.
- Which gems do I use?

138
00:06:19,746 --> 00:06:20,946
Yeah, it's so pretty.

139
00:06:20,947 --> 00:06:22,013
Whichever one you want.

140
00:06:22,014 --> 00:06:23,415
You're right.

141
00:06:23,416 --> 00:06:24,617
Yeah.

142
00:06:28,821 --> 00:06:30,123
Tatsuki, can you choose for me?

143
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:34,961
Then…

144
00:06:35,962 --> 00:06:37,662
You can use the example as a reference.

145
00:06:37,663 --> 00:06:39,198
- This pink color is so cute.
- Yeah.

146
00:06:41,901 --> 00:06:42,735
Here you go.

147
00:06:47,907 --> 00:06:50,209
Nene, will you be at the Yukanai Camp?

148
00:06:50,710 --> 00:06:51,610
Camp?

149
00:06:51,611 --> 00:06:53,845
Apparently, we're going to barbecue

150
00:06:53,846 --> 00:06:55,514
and do fireworks together.

151
00:06:55,515 --> 00:06:57,983
- That sounds like fun.
- Right?

152
00:06:57,984 --> 00:06:58,884
You should come.

153
00:06:58,885 --> 00:07:01,120
- Although we'll be staying the night here.
- Yeah.

154
00:07:01,621 --> 00:07:03,156
That's not so bad.

155
00:07:03,656 --> 00:07:06,658
But this is my last month here.

156
00:07:06,659 --> 00:07:07,926
Really?

157
00:07:07,927 --> 00:07:09,394
That's a bummer.

158
00:07:09,395 --> 00:07:10,295
Yeah.

159
00:07:10,296 --> 00:07:11,330
Oh no, I messed up.

160
00:07:12,632 --> 00:07:14,499
I did too. Look at mine.

161
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:16,668
- It's not aligned.
- Right?

162
00:07:16,669 --> 00:07:17,602
Oh no.

163
00:07:17,603 --> 00:07:19,172
Wow Nene, you're so good.

164
00:07:20,173 --> 00:07:21,807
- Very nice.
- Looks good.

165
00:07:21,808 --> 00:07:23,442
- Yeah.
- You're so good.

166
00:07:23,443 --> 00:07:26,312
But what color should I choose
for the horse?

167
00:07:28,581 --> 00:07:30,048
You can choose whatever you want.

168
00:07:30,049 --> 00:07:31,616
I chose green for mine.

169
00:07:31,617 --> 00:07:33,084
That's very you, Mao.

170
00:07:33,085 --> 00:07:34,853
It's so pretty.

171
00:07:34,854 --> 00:07:36,721
I think I'll go with purple.

172
00:07:36,722 --> 00:07:38,423
- Nice.
- That'll look cool.

173
00:07:38,424 --> 00:07:39,959
Nene, what's your favorite color?

174
00:07:42,094 --> 00:07:43,663
My favorite color…

175
00:08:00,346 --> 00:08:01,881
I have to head to my piano lesson.

176
00:08:04,083 --> 00:08:05,984
You can finish this next time.

177
00:08:05,985 --> 00:08:07,652
But this is her last month, right?

178
00:08:07,653 --> 00:08:10,223
If she wants to come,
she can come again next month. Okay?

179
00:08:11,357 --> 00:08:15,061
Bye.

180
00:08:27,073 --> 00:08:28,206
YUKANAI

181
00:08:28,207 --> 00:08:29,241
Diamond art, huh?

182
00:08:29,242 --> 00:08:30,141
Yeah.

183
00:08:30,142 --> 00:08:31,444
They look good.

184
00:08:33,045 --> 00:08:33,880
This is

185
00:08:34,747 --> 00:08:37,149
the one that Nene Tachibana
was working on.

186
00:08:38,217 --> 00:08:39,985
That's the girl that's leaving this month?

187
00:08:39,986 --> 00:08:40,820
Yes.

188
00:08:41,387 --> 00:08:43,088
It's detailed and precise.

189
00:08:43,089 --> 00:08:45,724
She plays the piano, so she seems
to be good with her hands.

190
00:08:45,725 --> 00:08:46,893
I see.

191
00:08:48,127 --> 00:08:49,862
What did you think when you saw this?

192
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:52,265
Well…

193
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,769
I felt like…

194
00:08:57,570 --> 00:08:59,771
it's really constrained.

195
00:08:59,772 --> 00:09:00,606
Constrained?

196
00:09:01,607 --> 00:09:03,408
I told her to freely choose the gems,

197
00:09:03,409 --> 00:09:05,210
but she had a hard time deciding.

198
00:09:05,211 --> 00:09:07,280
I wonder why that is.

199
00:09:09,482 --> 00:09:10,982
Maybe

200
00:09:10,983 --> 00:09:14,854
she's scared to express herself
freely and as she pleases?

201
00:09:17,456 --> 00:09:19,725
She might be lacking self-confidence.

202
00:09:23,496 --> 00:09:25,631
- What is it?
- Oh.

203
00:09:26,866 --> 00:09:28,100
Watching Nene

204
00:09:28,734 --> 00:09:31,170
<i>reminded me of Sora for some reason.</i>

205
00:09:38,377 --> 00:09:39,579
How's your son doing?

206
00:09:41,747 --> 00:09:44,183
It seems like he was discharged
from the hospital.

207
00:09:44,684 --> 00:09:45,585
That's all I know.

208
00:09:46,152 --> 00:09:47,253
- I see.
- Yeah.

209
00:09:50,723 --> 00:09:53,291
Tatsuki, you need a good night's rest.

210
00:09:53,292 --> 00:09:54,460
- Okay?
- Yeah.

211
00:10:10,910 --> 00:10:12,745
The competition is coming up soon.

212
00:10:14,513 --> 00:10:15,414
How's it going?

213
00:10:16,082 --> 00:10:18,050
Do you think
you can do pretty well this time?

214
00:10:20,052 --> 00:10:21,153
Not sure.

215
00:10:22,021 --> 00:10:24,724
Your teacher said you'll do well
if you keep up the good work.

216
00:10:26,292 --> 00:10:29,261
But I'm not as good as Big Sis.

217
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:33,165
There's no need
to compare yourself to her.

218
00:10:33,666 --> 00:10:35,067
After all, you're you.

219
00:10:36,435 --> 00:10:38,204
- Okay?
- Okay.

220
00:10:47,313 --> 00:10:50,249
I went to Yukanai today.

221
00:10:51,050 --> 00:10:51,884
What?

222
00:10:52,418 --> 00:10:53,252
Why?

223
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:55,254
I did some diamond art.

224
00:10:57,923 --> 00:10:58,858
Is that right?

225
00:11:07,533 --> 00:11:08,367
Nene,

226
00:11:09,435 --> 00:11:11,437
I've signed you up
for the summer study camp.

227
00:11:12,104 --> 00:11:12,938
- What?
- What?

228
00:11:13,906 --> 00:11:16,107
The cram school study camp?

229
00:11:16,108 --> 00:11:17,043
Yeah.

230
00:11:17,777 --> 00:11:20,179
You didn't do well
on that practice test the other day.

231
00:11:20,813 --> 00:11:22,948
There's no need to pressure her
about it right now.

232
00:11:23,949 --> 00:11:26,251
If she doesn't make up ground
during summer break,

233
00:11:26,252 --> 00:11:27,285
she'll fall behind.

234
00:11:27,286 --> 00:11:29,121
She hasn't even been able to go to school.

235
00:11:29,689 --> 00:11:32,457
I don't want to push her too hard
with things like study camp.

236
00:11:32,458 --> 00:11:33,559
Then

237
00:11:34,060 --> 00:11:36,062
is it okay if her grades keep dropping?

238
00:11:38,230 --> 00:11:40,332
The piano competition is coming up soon,

239
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:44,235
so I want her to focus on that right now.

240
00:11:44,236 --> 00:11:46,005
You prefer that too, right Nene?

241
00:11:50,743 --> 00:11:52,344
It's better to focus on her studies.

242
00:11:52,912 --> 00:11:55,513
- Is it really so?
- What about the entrance exam?

243
00:11:55,514 --> 00:11:56,348
She won't take it?

244
00:11:57,183 --> 00:11:58,317
That's not what I'm saying.

245
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:01,654
Nene.

246
00:12:02,321 --> 00:12:03,255
What do you want to do?

247
00:12:08,661 --> 00:12:09,661
YUKANAI

248
00:12:09,662 --> 00:12:10,596
NOW ACCEPTING NEW STUDENTS

249
00:12:14,133 --> 00:12:15,033
Hey!

250
00:12:15,034 --> 00:12:16,101
Anybody there?

251
00:12:16,102 --> 00:12:17,869
- What?
- Coming.

252
00:12:17,870 --> 00:12:19,804
- Help me.
- I'm coming.

253
00:12:19,805 --> 00:12:20,973
- I'll help.
- Here.

254
00:12:23,275 --> 00:12:24,843
What's all this?

255
00:12:24,844 --> 00:12:27,312
They're tents
for the Yukanai Camp next week!

256
00:12:27,313 --> 00:12:29,582
I had some extras at home in storage.

257
00:12:30,316 --> 00:12:32,951
Camping is all about the tent, right?

258
00:12:32,952 --> 00:12:35,653
Just pitching them in the yard
will really set the mood.

259
00:12:35,654 --> 00:12:36,955
Yeah.

260
00:12:36,956 --> 00:12:39,724
I guess we need to start
making preparations too.

261
00:12:39,725 --> 00:12:40,825
Right.

262
00:12:40,826 --> 00:12:43,194
We have to get ingredients
for the barbecue.

263
00:12:43,195 --> 00:12:45,363
- I want to do fireworks too.
- Sounds fun.

264
00:12:45,364 --> 00:12:46,531
What will you do, Ajicchan?

265
00:12:46,532 --> 00:12:47,632
Sweets workshop.

266
00:12:47,633 --> 00:12:49,768
We're planning to make ice cream together.

267
00:12:49,769 --> 00:12:51,736
That sounds fun. What about you, Soya?

268
00:12:51,737 --> 00:12:54,239
I'll be doing
a late-night gaming tournament.

269
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:56,207
I'm seriously going to win.

270
00:12:56,208 --> 00:12:57,877
I will be in charge of stargazing.

271
00:12:59,211 --> 00:13:00,879
There are lots of participants this year,

272
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:02,046
so I'm looking forward to it!

273
00:13:02,047 --> 00:13:03,948
I don't see Nene these days,
but is she coming?

274
00:13:03,949 --> 00:13:06,152
She'll be leaving
at the end of this month.

275
00:13:06,719 --> 00:13:08,019
I see.

276
00:13:08,020 --> 00:13:10,656
I'll try to at least
extend another invitation.

277
00:13:11,757 --> 00:13:14,426
Maybe I'll ask Shi-chan
to be the camp leader this year.

278
00:13:16,362 --> 00:13:18,663
Do you think I can handle
such an important role?

279
00:13:18,664 --> 00:13:20,732
- Shouldn't it be Mr. Tatsuki instead?
- No.

280
00:13:20,733 --> 00:13:22,568
Tatsuki isn't cut out
for that kind of stuff.

281
00:13:24,036 --> 00:13:24,870
Then

282
00:13:25,571 --> 00:13:26,638
Mr. Tatsuki,

283
00:13:26,639 --> 00:13:29,374
- you're in charge of the barbecue.
- Huh?

284
00:13:29,375 --> 00:13:30,275
What do I have to do?

285
00:13:30,276 --> 00:13:31,776
Buy the ingredients,

286
00:13:31,777 --> 00:13:33,678
then prepare and cook
on the day of the event.

287
00:13:33,679 --> 00:13:35,980
- We'll be counting on you.
- I have to do that alone?

288
00:13:35,981 --> 00:13:37,015
Yes.

289
00:13:37,016 --> 00:13:38,350
- What?
- Good luck.

290
00:13:39,051 --> 00:13:41,587
That'll be impossible!

291
00:13:42,755 --> 00:13:44,256
Hello, this is Tachibana.

292
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:46,725
This is Aomine from Yukanai.

293
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:49,027
- Hello.
<i>- Um…</i>

294
00:13:49,028 --> 00:13:51,763
An event called Yukanai Camp
is coming up, can Nene attend

295
00:13:51,764 --> 00:13:53,933
before she leaves at the end of the month?

296
00:13:55,167 --> 00:13:56,201
I'm sorry.

297
00:13:56,202 --> 00:13:58,270
She's going to be at a study camp
on that day.

298
00:13:59,405 --> 00:14:00,505
I see.

299
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:02,842
- Thank you for your time.
<i>- Thank you.</i>

300
00:14:04,710 --> 00:14:06,144
Um…

301
00:14:06,145 --> 00:14:09,248
How has Nene been doing lately?

302
00:14:10,149 --> 00:14:12,384
She's doing well.

303
00:14:13,886 --> 00:14:15,221
I'm glad to hear that.

304
00:14:16,121 --> 00:14:18,323
Thank you for your time. Bye.

305
00:14:18,324 --> 00:14:19,892
<i>Bye.</i>

306
00:14:29,668 --> 00:14:30,669
Nene?

307
00:14:33,505 --> 00:14:35,140
- Tatsuki.
- Off to your piano lesson?

308
00:14:36,542 --> 00:14:38,611
- I have cram school today.
- I see.

309
00:14:40,446 --> 00:14:41,580
What were you doing?

310
00:14:43,415 --> 00:14:44,717
I'm out shopping

311
00:14:45,217 --> 00:14:46,417
to buy things for our camp.

312
00:14:46,418 --> 00:14:48,821
It's so heavy my arms are about
to fall off.

313
00:14:49,989 --> 00:14:51,090
I wish I could go.

314
00:14:52,057 --> 00:14:52,925
You should come.

315
00:14:54,927 --> 00:14:56,161
But I didn't sign up.

316
00:14:56,729 --> 00:14:58,463
You can still come.

317
00:14:58,464 --> 00:14:59,832
You can finish the diamond art.

318
00:15:02,067 --> 00:15:03,202
But

319
00:15:03,736 --> 00:15:05,537
I have to go to the study camp too.

320
00:15:07,106 --> 00:15:08,207
I see.

321
00:15:08,707 --> 00:15:11,176
EXAM PREP CRAM SCHOOL

322
00:15:13,545 --> 00:15:14,380
Bye.

323
00:15:15,814 --> 00:15:16,649
See you again.

324
00:15:28,594 --> 00:15:29,662
Nene.

325
00:15:32,798 --> 00:15:34,400
Want to work on the diamond art?

326
00:15:39,638 --> 00:15:40,906
Here you go.

327
00:15:43,475 --> 00:15:45,010
Use whatever color gem you want.

328
00:15:46,979 --> 00:15:48,881
Which color should I choose?

329
00:15:53,218 --> 00:15:54,153
Do you have gold?

330
00:15:55,721 --> 00:15:58,424
Gold?

331
00:15:59,358 --> 00:16:00,492
I don't think so.

332
00:16:02,261 --> 00:16:03,362
You like gold?

333
00:16:07,866 --> 00:16:10,002
Yeah, since it represents number one.

334
00:16:10,569 --> 00:16:11,570
I see.

335
00:16:14,473 --> 00:16:15,407
Then

336
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:17,076
I'll make sure to buy it.

337
00:16:36,095 --> 00:16:37,228
Thank you.

338
00:16:37,229 --> 00:16:38,664
You're welcome.

339
00:16:41,367 --> 00:16:44,769
Can I take this home once I finish?

340
00:16:44,770 --> 00:16:45,971
Of course.

341
00:16:47,506 --> 00:16:50,042
Your mom and dad will be surprised
with your masterpiece.

342
00:16:52,778 --> 00:16:56,315
But I'll get in trouble
for skipping cram school.

343
00:17:00,185 --> 00:17:01,020
Really?

344
00:17:06,859 --> 00:17:09,728
You used two different colors
for the horses, huh?

345
00:17:11,263 --> 00:17:12,865
- Is it weird?
- No.

346
00:17:13,365 --> 00:17:14,633
It's such a great idea.

347
00:17:16,935 --> 00:17:18,370
Why did you choose these colors?

348
00:17:24,343 --> 00:17:26,345
Mom likes pink,

349
00:17:28,447 --> 00:17:32,251
and I think this other color
will make Dad happy.

350
00:17:39,858 --> 00:17:40,726
That's nice.

351
00:18:10,155 --> 00:18:11,355
I'm home.

352
00:18:11,356 --> 00:18:12,291
Welcome back.

353
00:18:12,791 --> 00:18:13,625
‎I'm done.

354
00:18:15,194 --> 00:18:16,161
Nene,

355
00:18:17,229 --> 00:18:18,630
why didn't you go to cram school?

356
00:18:19,631 --> 00:18:21,567
They called to tell us you didn't show up.

357
00:18:23,202 --> 00:18:24,136
I'm sorry.

358
00:18:25,170 --> 00:18:26,438
Where've you been until now?

359
00:18:28,440 --> 00:18:29,274
Yukanai.

360
00:18:30,309 --> 00:18:31,243
Why?

361
00:18:31,743 --> 00:18:32,911
What were you doing there?

362
00:18:33,412 --> 00:18:36,281
We're fine with you going there,

363
00:18:36,882 --> 00:18:38,016
but just know this,

364
00:18:38,517 --> 00:18:39,985
you have responsibilities too.

365
00:18:46,925 --> 00:18:48,160
I'm sorry.

366
00:18:48,727 --> 00:18:52,396
I'm not asking
for anything difficult here.

367
00:18:52,397 --> 00:18:55,500
If school isn't a good fit for you,
then it's fine that you don't go.

368
00:18:55,501 --> 00:18:59,037
But in exchange, you need to go
to cram school and study.

369
00:18:59,538 --> 00:19:01,206
You're taking the entrance exam, right?

370
00:19:03,642 --> 00:19:07,579
And yet, if you go around saying
you can't do this and you can't do that,

371
00:19:08,313 --> 00:19:10,115
that's being unreasonable, isn't it?

372
00:19:11,316 --> 00:19:13,117
What do you plan to do from here on out?

373
00:19:13,118 --> 00:19:14,418
Let's not get into that now.

374
00:19:14,419 --> 00:19:15,721
Why not?

375
00:19:16,388 --> 00:19:18,356
I'm saying this for her sake.

376
00:19:18,357 --> 00:19:19,957
She can study

377
00:19:19,958 --> 00:19:22,260
at her own pace
and do it little by little.

378
00:19:22,261 --> 00:19:24,328
Things turned out this way

379
00:19:24,329 --> 00:19:26,063
because you keep coddling her like that.

380
00:19:26,064 --> 00:19:27,798
As if it's my fault?

381
00:19:27,799 --> 00:19:30,201
You keep on pressuring her like that
all the time…

382
00:19:30,202 --> 00:19:33,138
- So it's my fault?
- I didn't say that.

383
00:20:44,710 --> 00:20:49,147
Stack small pieces of charcoal
in a pyramid atop the fire starter…

384
00:20:49,681 --> 00:20:50,882
A pyramid?

385
00:20:52,117 --> 00:20:54,685
We got a call from Nene's mom.

386
00:20:54,686 --> 00:20:55,653
What did she say?

387
00:20:55,654 --> 00:20:56,822
She was upset.

388
00:20:57,322 --> 00:21:00,025
Were you aware
that Nene skipped cram school?

389
00:21:00,759 --> 00:21:03,561
‎-Yeah.
‎-No wonder she was upset.

390
00:21:03,562 --> 00:21:05,963
Nene didn't want to go,
so there's nothing I can do.

391
00:21:05,964 --> 00:21:07,031
Yeah…

392
00:21:07,032 --> 00:21:09,567
But even so, you should've
at least reported it.

393
00:21:09,568 --> 00:21:11,002
Hey everyone.

394
00:21:11,003 --> 00:21:12,738
- Hello.
- Hey.

395
00:21:13,505 --> 00:21:16,074
- Here's what you asked for.
- Thank you.

396
00:21:17,709 --> 00:21:19,310
Sixty colors should be enough, right?

397
00:21:19,311 --> 00:21:20,612
More than enough.

398
00:21:21,113 --> 00:21:22,280
By the way,

399
00:21:22,281 --> 00:21:24,916
what happened to Nene after that?

400
00:21:26,318 --> 00:21:29,921
She took the finished diamond art
home with her.

401
00:21:30,522 --> 00:21:31,423
I found it.

402
00:21:32,524 --> 00:21:33,425
Here it is.

403
00:21:35,761 --> 00:21:38,330
- She chose the colors pink and brown?
- Yes.

404
00:21:39,398 --> 00:21:44,236
‎She used brown and pink because
‎those are her parents' favorite colors.

405
00:21:45,170 --> 00:21:47,439
But I guess
they're not Nene's favorite colors.

406
00:21:48,707 --> 00:21:50,142
I wonder what this means.

407
00:21:57,049 --> 00:22:00,184
<i>She said that she likes the color gold.</i>

408
00:22:00,185 --> 00:22:02,387
But I wonder if she said that
with her parents in mind.

409
00:22:03,655 --> 00:22:04,990
I see.

410
00:22:05,691 --> 00:22:09,361
I wonder how she really feels about
leaving Yukanai.

411
00:22:12,931 --> 00:22:15,901
Should I go
visit Nene at her house tomorrow?

412
00:22:18,203 --> 00:22:21,706
It's better not to interfere too much
in other people's family matters.

413
00:22:21,707 --> 00:22:23,908
I have no intention
of interfering unnecessarily.

414
00:22:23,909 --> 00:22:25,544
Then why do you want to go there?

415
00:22:26,578 --> 00:22:27,879
Because…

416
00:22:29,348 --> 00:22:31,850
I just want to do whatever I can.

417
00:22:32,351 --> 00:22:36,755
After all, Yukanai might be
a precious place for Nene.

418
00:22:39,624 --> 00:22:42,194
Let's leave this up to Shi-chan for now.

419
00:22:44,896 --> 00:22:47,232
But be careful when dealing with Nene.

420
00:22:48,233 --> 00:22:49,101
Yes.

421
00:22:53,805 --> 00:22:54,705
Thank you

422
00:22:54,706 --> 00:22:57,141
for taking time to meet with me.

423
00:22:57,142 --> 00:22:58,110
My pleasure.

424
00:22:58,910 --> 00:23:03,781
But we still plan to leave Yukanai
at the end of this month.

425
00:23:03,782 --> 00:23:05,016
I'm sorry.

426
00:23:05,617 --> 00:23:06,451
No problem at all.

427
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:09,388
Where is Nene right now?

428
00:23:11,690 --> 00:23:13,591
She's in her room.

429
00:23:13,592 --> 00:23:15,594
I just want to let her be for now.

430
00:23:16,361 --> 00:23:19,897
I think
she's a bit overwhelmed right now.

431
00:23:19,898 --> 00:23:20,798
NENE

432
00:23:20,799 --> 00:23:23,402
She's still going to cram school
and piano lessons, right?

433
00:23:24,002 --> 00:23:24,836
Yes.

434
00:23:25,904 --> 00:23:27,171
To be honest,

435
00:23:27,172 --> 00:23:30,308
I feel like cram school
is quite a burden for her.

436
00:23:30,809 --> 00:23:32,543
After all, she stopped going to school

437
00:23:32,544 --> 00:23:34,079
because she didn't enjoy studying.

438
00:23:35,347 --> 00:23:36,181
That’s why

439
00:23:36,748 --> 00:23:39,985
I think she should focus on piano,
since that's something she enjoys.

440
00:23:41,620 --> 00:23:43,755
Did Nene say that she enjoys it?

441
00:23:44,790 --> 00:23:46,792
I can tell just by watching her.

442
00:23:50,362 --> 00:23:51,196
I've decided

443
00:23:52,197 --> 00:23:54,533
to take a leave of absence from work.

444
00:23:56,034 --> 00:23:57,468
As a parent,

445
00:23:57,469 --> 00:24:00,771
I intend to face this issue with her
and help her out.

446
00:24:00,772 --> 00:24:02,107
So please rest assured.

447
00:24:06,244 --> 00:24:07,978
I'm sorry,

448
00:24:07,979 --> 00:24:10,916
- but can I use the restroom?
- Yes.

449
00:25:04,236 --> 00:25:06,103
YU

450
00:25:06,104 --> 00:25:08,607
I HEARD SORA WAS DISCHARGED,
BUT HOW'S HE DOING?

451
00:25:12,611 --> 00:25:13,778
Hey Sora!

452
00:25:18,083 --> 00:25:19,850
- Sora!
- Don't come in here!

453
00:25:19,851 --> 00:25:20,986
Go away!

454
00:25:22,621 --> 00:25:23,855
Open the door, Sora!

455
00:25:24,356 --> 00:25:25,290
Shut up!

456
00:25:56,788 --> 00:25:58,557
The study camp starts today, right?

457
00:26:00,058 --> 00:26:01,892
It's almost time to go.

458
00:26:01,893 --> 00:26:02,861
I wonder where she is.

459
00:26:07,332 --> 00:26:08,166
Hey.

460
00:26:08,900 --> 00:26:09,734
Are you ready to go?

461
00:26:10,902 --> 00:26:11,937
I'm coming in.

462
00:26:14,973 --> 00:26:17,175
What's the matter? Do you not feel well?

463
00:26:19,210 --> 00:26:20,178
I'm okay.

464
00:26:22,447 --> 00:26:23,847
I'll take you to the station.

465
00:26:23,848 --> 00:26:24,683
Let's hurry.

466
00:26:27,586 --> 00:26:28,420
Okay.

467
00:26:34,159 --> 00:26:35,727
Do your best.

468
00:26:37,462 --> 00:26:38,663
- Thanks.
- Sure.

469
00:26:50,809 --> 00:26:52,176
CRAM SCHOOL
FOR MIDDLE SCHOOL ENTRANCE EXAMS

470
00:26:52,177 --> 00:26:53,745
Good morning.

471
00:26:54,346 --> 00:26:55,180
Yes.

472
00:26:58,016 --> 00:27:01,419
YUKANAI CAMP

473
00:27:10,862 --> 00:27:11,862
All right.

474
00:27:11,863 --> 00:27:14,866
Hello!

475
00:27:16,334 --> 00:27:18,135
Hey!

476
00:27:18,136 --> 00:27:19,303
Let's play Mario Kart.

477
00:27:19,304 --> 00:27:20,537
There's a game in the evening.

478
00:27:20,538 --> 00:27:21,839
I want to practice for that.

479
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:22,940
What?

480
00:27:22,941 --> 00:27:24,775
You're using me just to practice?

481
00:27:24,776 --> 00:27:25,909
- Don't forget.
- Attention!

482
00:27:25,910 --> 00:27:28,012
Whoever's free, come out to the yard.

483
00:27:28,013 --> 00:27:29,880
- Okay.
- Come help us.

484
00:27:29,881 --> 00:27:32,016
This will fit about four to five.

485
00:27:32,017 --> 00:27:33,684
This is exciting.

486
00:27:33,685 --> 00:27:36,687
I've been wanting to do stargazing.

487
00:27:36,688 --> 00:27:37,988
Do you know much about stars?

488
00:27:37,989 --> 00:27:39,991
Not at all. I only know the North Star.

489
00:27:40,825 --> 00:27:42,526
- I see.
- But

490
00:27:42,527 --> 00:27:44,863
there are apps that can help us out.

491
00:27:45,930 --> 00:27:47,498
I can search for the stars I want to see.

492
00:27:47,499 --> 00:27:48,900
That's so handy.

493
00:27:49,901 --> 00:27:50,802
The tent looks nice.

494
00:27:51,469 --> 00:27:52,936
Oh, it's a telescope!

495
00:27:52,937 --> 00:27:55,639
Yeah, Professor Mikumo brought this.

496
00:27:55,640 --> 00:27:56,940
- Wow.
- Yeah.

497
00:27:56,941 --> 00:27:58,742
I found it at a flea market.

498
00:27:58,743 --> 00:27:59,810
Hey,

499
00:27:59,811 --> 00:28:00,879
someone help me out.

500
00:28:01,446 --> 00:28:03,347
I'll help.

501
00:28:03,348 --> 00:28:04,515
Thanks, Umine.

502
00:28:04,516 --> 00:28:05,416
Then

503
00:28:05,417 --> 00:28:07,051
- can you bring the firewood?
- Firewood?

504
00:28:07,052 --> 00:28:08,018
- Yeah.
- This?

505
00:28:08,019 --> 00:28:08,919
Yeah, the same one.

506
00:28:08,920 --> 00:28:09,953
Okay.

507
00:28:09,954 --> 00:28:11,088
- Thanks.
- Tatsuki.

508
00:28:11,089 --> 00:28:12,456
Can I do the fireworks?

509
00:28:12,457 --> 00:28:15,193
Yeah, but it won't be as pretty
if you do it right now.

510
00:28:16,461 --> 00:28:18,696
We can stay awake
as long as we want today, right?

511
00:28:18,697 --> 00:28:20,264
Yup, as long as you want.

512
00:28:20,265 --> 00:28:21,866
Then I'll stay awake all night.

513
00:28:22,767 --> 00:28:25,102
People who say that
always fall asleep first.

514
00:28:25,103 --> 00:28:27,138
Keep shaking.

515
00:28:28,006 --> 00:28:30,107
All right.

516
00:28:30,108 --> 00:28:31,876
Let's take it out of the bag.

517
00:28:33,211 --> 00:28:34,712
- It's done!
- Wow!

518
00:28:34,713 --> 00:28:35,979
Wow.

519
00:28:35,980 --> 00:28:37,448
Let's all eat this tonight.

520
00:28:37,449 --> 00:28:39,616
Hooray!

521
00:28:39,617 --> 00:28:40,517
<i>Begin.</i>

522
00:28:40,518 --> 00:28:41,518
Go!

523
00:28:41,519 --> 00:28:43,587
Let's all eliminate Ei-chan first.

524
00:28:43,588 --> 00:28:44,688
Good idea.

525
00:28:44,689 --> 00:28:46,725
Don't bully the elderly.

526
00:28:47,826 --> 00:28:50,428
Hey, did Nene show up?

527
00:28:50,995 --> 00:28:52,097
Nope, she's not here.

528
00:28:52,664 --> 00:28:54,565
I see.

529
00:28:54,566 --> 00:28:55,999
- Thanks.
- Sure.

530
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:57,468
Go for it.

531
00:28:57,469 --> 00:28:59,436
Go, go!

532
00:28:59,437 --> 00:29:00,370
You can do it.

533
00:29:00,371 --> 00:29:02,240
- You can do it.
- You can do it.

534
00:29:03,875 --> 00:29:05,509
What's wrong with this?

535
00:29:05,510 --> 00:29:06,677
Just a little bit more.

536
00:29:06,678 --> 00:29:08,979
We can't eat unless you get
the fire started.

537
00:29:08,980 --> 00:29:10,515
- Just wait a minute.
- How's it going?

538
00:29:11,082 --> 00:29:14,251
I piled the charcoal
in the form of a pyramid.

539
00:29:14,252 --> 00:29:15,552
- But…
- Oh.

540
00:29:15,553 --> 00:29:17,721
There's no way
air can pass through like this.

541
00:29:17,722 --> 00:29:18,922
Huh?

542
00:29:18,923 --> 00:29:20,124
You can do it.

543
00:29:20,125 --> 00:29:22,127
All right. It's ready.

544
00:29:22,761 --> 00:29:25,429
- Soya, you're a genius.
- Thank you.

545
00:29:25,430 --> 00:29:26,564
Good job.

546
00:29:28,333 --> 00:29:29,233
Okay.

547
00:29:29,234 --> 00:29:31,102
All right, let's start grilling.

548
00:29:33,972 --> 00:29:36,206
- It looks delicious.
- I can't wait to eat paella.

549
00:29:36,207 --> 00:29:37,775
Ready?

550
00:29:37,776 --> 00:29:39,444
Open sesame!

551
00:29:40,111 --> 00:29:41,411
It's paella.

552
00:29:41,412 --> 00:29:42,513
It looks so good.

553
00:29:42,514 --> 00:29:44,081
It's paella.

554
00:29:44,082 --> 00:29:45,649
It's so good!

555
00:29:45,650 --> 00:29:46,850
It's super yummy!

556
00:29:46,851 --> 00:29:48,886
I want to roast a marshmallow.

557
00:29:48,887 --> 00:29:50,988
I'm going to grill a sausage.

558
00:29:50,989 --> 00:29:52,356
- Go ahead.
- It's time

559
00:29:52,357 --> 00:29:54,192
- to grill some corn!
- Yay!

560
00:29:55,160 --> 00:29:57,961
It's time for corn.

561
00:29:57,962 --> 00:29:59,696
Where did Tatsuki go?

562
00:29:59,697 --> 00:30:00,764
Oh?

563
00:30:00,765 --> 00:30:01,833
He ran away, huh?

564
00:30:02,801 --> 00:30:04,836
Yup, he's not fit to be a leader at all.

565
00:30:31,262 --> 00:30:34,265
<i>The person you have called
is unable to answer right now…</i>

566
00:30:42,207 --> 00:30:44,042
YU

567
00:30:50,081 --> 00:30:50,915
Hello.

568
00:30:51,916 --> 00:30:53,852
I told you not to contact me anymore.

569
00:30:54,686 --> 00:30:55,620
How's Sora?

570
00:30:56,721 --> 00:30:58,189
How's he doing? Is he all right?

571
00:31:00,525 --> 00:31:01,626
You know…

572
00:31:03,461 --> 00:31:05,196
If you truly care about him,

573
00:31:05,697 --> 00:31:07,298
stay away from us forever.

574
00:31:33,458 --> 00:31:34,559
‎Hey.

575
00:31:35,526 --> 00:31:37,662
This was made
with gems of my favorite color.

576
00:31:38,162 --> 00:31:40,031
Tatsuki, you made this, right?

577
00:31:44,369 --> 00:31:45,403
That reminds me!

578
00:31:46,004 --> 00:31:47,405
Take a look at this.

579
00:31:51,142 --> 00:31:52,510
Ta-da!

580
00:31:53,478 --> 00:31:55,580
- It's beautiful.
- Isn't it?

581
00:31:56,447 --> 00:31:57,482
Go ahead and use it.

582
00:32:02,287 --> 00:32:03,588
I was supposed

583
00:32:05,623 --> 00:32:07,692
to go to the cram school study camp today.

584
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:10,395
Good morning.

585
00:32:11,930 --> 00:32:12,864
I'm sorry,

586
00:32:15,133 --> 00:32:17,068
but I won't be going to the study camp.

587
00:32:17,769 --> 00:32:19,170
You decided not to go?

588
00:32:23,141 --> 00:32:24,642
I hate studying and playing the piano.

589
00:32:25,410 --> 00:32:26,244
What?

590
00:32:27,078 --> 00:32:28,346
I thought you liked piano.

591
00:32:29,013 --> 00:32:29,948
I hate it.

592
00:32:31,716 --> 00:32:32,717
I see.

593
00:32:34,919 --> 00:32:36,087
It must've been tough for you.

594
00:32:45,964 --> 00:32:46,798
Then,

595
00:32:49,267 --> 00:32:52,502
let's take time to enjoy this later.

596
00:32:52,503 --> 00:32:53,871
Let's enjoy the barbecue first.

597
00:32:54,739 --> 00:32:56,174
Hurry or there'll be no meat left.

598
00:32:58,409 --> 00:32:59,377
Let's go.

599
00:32:59,877 --> 00:33:02,480
All right, let's get ready
to crack the watermelon open.

600
00:33:02,981 --> 00:33:05,849
Here's another skewer.

601
00:33:05,850 --> 00:33:08,286
- Take one, Nene.
- Thank you.

602
00:33:08,853 --> 00:33:10,588
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

603
00:33:11,622 --> 00:33:13,358
What? Oh no.

604
00:33:13,925 --> 00:33:16,127
Oh no! It's stuck!

605
00:33:16,627 --> 00:33:18,997
You can remove it using baking soda.

606
00:33:19,564 --> 00:33:21,331
I need a different solution.

607
00:33:21,332 --> 00:33:23,567
Go! Go!

608
00:33:23,568 --> 00:33:25,869
Go! You can do it.

609
00:33:25,870 --> 00:33:28,439
Go! Go!

610
00:33:31,943 --> 00:33:33,610
Yeah!

611
00:33:33,611 --> 00:33:35,046
Let's try it.

612
00:33:35,546 --> 00:33:36,613
It's so good.

613
00:33:36,614 --> 00:33:37,648
It's really good.

614
00:33:40,585 --> 00:33:43,521
BLUE FLAME
JAPAN BLUE

615
00:33:49,460 --> 00:33:50,762
This one is so cute.

616
00:34:00,772 --> 00:34:01,939
How pretty.

617
00:34:18,990 --> 00:34:20,358
Your mom doesn't know you're here?

618
00:34:22,326 --> 00:34:24,195
She thinks I'm at study camp.

619
00:34:25,263 --> 00:34:27,331
That's not good.

620
00:34:27,832 --> 00:34:29,634
- I'm going to call your mom.
- Wait.

621
00:34:32,336 --> 00:34:33,538
Don't tell her.

622
00:34:35,239 --> 00:34:36,140
But

623
00:34:36,774 --> 00:34:38,209
your mom will be worried.

624
00:34:40,778 --> 00:34:42,313
I don't want to go home.

625
00:34:48,052 --> 00:34:49,620
Then you don't have to.

626
00:34:50,254 --> 00:34:52,123
I'll discuss it with your mom.

627
00:34:53,324 --> 00:34:54,325
Okay?

628
00:34:58,529 --> 00:35:00,898
What? She didn't go to study camp?

629
00:35:01,466 --> 00:35:02,699
Why?

630
00:35:02,700 --> 00:35:05,303
I just got a call telling me
that she's at Yukanai.

631
00:35:06,838 --> 00:35:08,538
- I'm going to go get her.
- Wait.

632
00:35:08,539 --> 00:35:09,506
What?

633
00:35:09,507 --> 00:35:12,876
There's a camping event
going on at Yukanai today, so she'll be

634
00:35:12,877 --> 00:35:13,910
staying the night.

635
00:35:13,911 --> 00:35:15,546
What do you mean?

636
00:35:16,147 --> 00:35:19,750
As her parents
we should be going there to pick her up.

637
00:35:22,220 --> 00:35:23,453
Fine.

638
00:35:23,454 --> 00:35:25,289
But I'll go instead.

639
00:35:38,703 --> 00:35:41,772
All right.

640
00:35:44,775 --> 00:35:46,110
The one I did the other day…

641
00:35:48,579 --> 00:35:50,748
Did your dad and mom like it?

642
00:35:56,521 --> 00:35:57,588
I didn't show it to them.

643
00:36:00,892 --> 00:36:01,759
I see.

644
00:36:12,236 --> 00:36:13,137
What's the matter?

645
00:36:16,774 --> 00:36:18,609
I worked so hard to make it,

646
00:36:21,379 --> 00:36:22,747
but I ended up destroying it.

647
00:36:45,203 --> 00:36:47,138
Even though I worked so hard on it.

648
00:36:55,112 --> 00:36:56,113
Nene, what is it

649
00:36:57,114 --> 00:36:58,015
that you want to do?

650
00:37:00,685 --> 00:37:01,919
I don't know.

651
00:37:17,935 --> 00:37:19,303
You can do whatever you want.

652
00:38:00,077 --> 00:38:01,545
You're not going to use gold?

653
00:38:08,519 --> 00:38:09,754
The truth is…

654
00:38:15,726 --> 00:38:17,662
my favorite color is blue.

655
00:38:26,737 --> 00:38:27,838
Okay.

656
00:38:38,149 --> 00:38:41,319
YUKANAI

657
00:38:48,459 --> 00:38:49,694
Good evening.

658
00:38:50,227 --> 00:38:51,062
Good evening.

659
00:38:53,030 --> 00:38:55,032
- Come in.
- Thank you.

660
00:38:57,702 --> 00:38:58,602
Um…

661
00:38:59,970 --> 00:39:01,539
she just fell asleep.

662
00:39:02,039 --> 00:39:03,840
Can you take her back tomorrow?

663
00:39:03,841 --> 00:39:05,475
I'm taking her back tonight.

664
00:39:05,476 --> 00:39:07,043
Please wait a second.

665
00:39:07,044 --> 00:39:08,679
- Nene is inside, right?
- Wait.

666
00:39:09,547 --> 00:39:12,183
Nene is saying
that she doesn't want to go home.

667
00:39:12,983 --> 00:39:13,818
What?

668
00:39:15,086 --> 00:39:17,520
She would never say something like that.

669
00:39:17,521 --> 00:39:18,522
That's probably because

670
00:39:20,157 --> 00:39:22,259
she can't bring herself to tell you that.

671
00:39:38,776 --> 00:39:41,612
She did a diamond art project.

672
00:39:45,383 --> 00:39:48,085
I told her to freely choose
whatever color she wants,

673
00:39:48,652 --> 00:39:51,989
but at first she would only try
to replicate the sample.

674
00:39:53,524 --> 00:39:55,959
It made me wonder if she was too afraid

675
00:39:55,960 --> 00:39:57,995
to express her own will.

676
00:40:00,965 --> 00:40:03,334
Even when I told her
to choose any color she wanted,

677
00:40:04,402 --> 00:40:06,070
she chose the brown that would make

678
00:40:06,937 --> 00:40:09,807
her dad happy
and the pink that her mom would like.

679
00:40:11,075 --> 00:40:13,811
What's the meaning behind that?

680
00:40:18,516 --> 00:40:20,483
I believe she's trying to do everything

681
00:40:20,484 --> 00:40:22,820
in order to please her parents.

682
00:40:27,358 --> 00:40:28,692
Does anything come to mind?

683
00:40:31,495 --> 00:40:34,665
My husband and I have discussions
about her quite often.

684
00:40:35,766 --> 00:40:37,935
He wants to send her to cram school,

685
00:40:38,436 --> 00:40:40,438
while I want her to take up the piano.

686
00:40:41,539 --> 00:40:44,775
We do clash over our differing viewpoints…

687
00:40:45,476 --> 00:40:49,612
But I personally believe
that the best approach is to simply let

688
00:40:49,613 --> 00:40:51,315
Nene do whatever she wants to do.

689
00:40:52,383 --> 00:40:54,485
And that it is my role as her parent

690
00:40:54,985 --> 00:40:56,954
to help her cultivate those talents.

691
00:40:58,322 --> 00:40:59,557
Her talents?

692
00:41:01,158 --> 00:41:03,894
She loves playing the piano.

693
00:41:11,669 --> 00:41:12,703
Nene.

694
00:41:26,016 --> 00:41:27,618
I hate the piano.

695
00:41:31,956 --> 00:41:34,592
I can never become as good as Big Sis,

696
00:41:37,294 --> 00:41:39,363
and honestly,
I don't want to play the piano at all.

697
00:41:41,298 --> 00:41:42,233
Then

698
00:41:42,933 --> 00:41:45,536
- why didn't you say so?
- There's no way I could.

699
00:41:46,570 --> 00:41:50,274
If I do, you and Dad
will start fighting again.

700
00:41:58,115 --> 00:41:59,849
Why don't we let her stay here tonight?

701
00:41:59,850 --> 00:42:00,684
No,

702
00:42:01,252 --> 00:42:03,686
we've already canceled our enrollment,
so it's okay.

703
00:42:03,687 --> 00:42:05,890
- But we don't mind at all--
- Tatsuki.

704
00:42:07,791 --> 00:42:08,993
It's okay.

705
00:42:13,097 --> 00:42:14,498
Are you sure?

706
00:42:18,202 --> 00:42:19,737
I'll go home.

707
00:42:23,140 --> 00:42:24,775
Sorry for bothering you late at night.

708
00:42:26,110 --> 00:42:26,944
Go get changed.

709
00:42:30,180 --> 00:42:31,215
Thank you.

710
00:42:52,603 --> 00:42:54,038
It's worrisome, isn't it?

711
00:43:13,123 --> 00:43:15,092
TACHIBANA

712
00:43:39,316 --> 00:43:41,185
Nene, what's wrong?

713
00:43:43,821 --> 00:43:44,755
Hey.

714
00:43:45,723 --> 00:43:48,626
Nene. Nene, open up.

715
00:43:53,631 --> 00:43:54,465
Mr. Tatsuki.

716
00:43:55,466 --> 00:43:57,267
Mr. Tatsuki! It's about Nene…

717
00:43:57,968 --> 00:43:58,802
‎What?

718
00:44:01,872 --> 00:44:02,805
Thanks for coming.

719
00:44:02,806 --> 00:44:03,641
No problem.

720
00:44:05,909 --> 00:44:08,545
I don't know what to do anymore.

721
00:44:17,221 --> 00:44:19,456
Don't come in here! Go away!

722
00:44:21,725 --> 00:44:24,561
Sora! Open the door, Sora!

723
00:44:27,264 --> 00:44:28,232
I

724
00:44:29,967 --> 00:44:31,068
don't know what to do either.

725
00:44:32,069 --> 00:44:33,437
What?

726
00:44:35,005 --> 00:44:35,839
But…

727
00:44:39,276 --> 00:44:40,811
I have to do something.

728
00:45:06,036 --> 00:45:07,503
PREVIEW OF THE NEXT EPISODE

729
00:45:07,504 --> 00:45:09,672
‎THIS DRAMA IS FICTION

730
00:45:09,673 --> 00:45:10,974
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita
